news.title: Land prices in Amaravati go north
news.para: The recent developments in Telangana came as a trigger for the market movement and they are driving the prices up in Amaravati, according to realtors.

news.title: Hyderabad: Twist in plot for buyers of used homes
news.para: Post-pandemic, the prices of second-hand homes have surged, nearly matching the cost of newly constructed apartments pre-Covid-19.

news.title: Secunderabad: Over 5,000 unassessed SCB properties to enter tax wing records
news.para: Recently, SCB engineering wing transferred the data of these over 5,000 properties to SCB tax wing, to consider as official property and update the records.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRCL gets 38,000 sq ft Mahim plot on lease for commercial use
news.para: In a Government Resolution issued on Thursday, the state revenue department said the land is being leased at a nominal rate, though it does not mention the rate.

news.title: Delhi municipal corporation took action against 111 illegal constructions since Dec 1
news.para: ​The civic body carried out demolition and sealing work in areas such as Dera Mandi, Aya Nagar, Bhati, Chhatarpur, Mehrauli, Neb Sarai, Green Park, Safdarjung Enclave, Greater Kailash Part 1 and 2, Mandi Gaon, and Bhati Mines.

news.title: ICICI Securities leases over 1.88 lakh sq ft office in Mindspace Juinagar for 12 years
news.para: The ICICI Bank subsidiary has leased the office space spread across five floors in one of the towers of the IT park from Newfound Properties & Leasing, a subsidiary of real estate developer K Raheja Corp.

news.title: Rain harvesting in residential areas in Madhya Pradesh: HC disposes plea
news.para: Advocate Aditya Sanghi, in his public interest litigation (PIL) filed in 2019, has said that article 21 of the Constitution guarantees right to life. There can be no life without water. But, the water table is constantly going down. At several places, it has touched 500 metres or more.

news.title: Delhi environment minister directs effective implementation of stage-3 GRAP curbs
news.para: Addressing a press conference here, the minister said that air quality in Delhi deteriorated from very poor to the severe category on Friday due to low temperatures and calm winds.

news.title: ED files prosecution complaint against Premia Projects, Solitaire Infomedia under PMLA act
news.para: The directors have been identified as Tarun Shienh, Rekha Shienh, Luxmy Rajput and Charanjeet Singh Dani. The prosecution complaint has been filed in the Special Court, PMLA, Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: Noida lift crash: Five employees of Awfis arrested for negligence
news.para: Those arrested have been identified as Mohit Pant, Abhineet Mathur, Ramesh Chandra, Neetu Chandna Bisht and Shraddha Thapa. All of them are employees of co-working space provider Awfis, according to police.

news.title: Bengaluru: Loose control on newly fixed BTM Layout road
news.para: Residents of area say low-quality material used has made gravel come off in days, posing bigger risk to commuters.

news.title: DDA approaches HC against stay on demolition of apartments
news.para: Acting on a petition by nine residents of the apartments in Mukherjee Nagar, Delhi High Court had last month ordered DDA not to take any coercive steps against the residents who have challenged the authority’s unilateral move.

news.title: Builders in Maharashtra benefiting from delay in rental housing scheme projects: Activists
news.para: Four such projects have total 15,720 flats developed in 88 separate buildings, a few of which are under construction. Of these 3,234 flats are of 320 sq ft and 12,486 flats are of 160 sq ft.

news.title: Resolve all property tax complaints: ULB director to Gurugram civic body
news.para: The move came after residents complained about the pending status of their property tax objections and applications. Yadav said the officers and clerks, who delay property tax files, will face action.

news.title: Hand over Hukumchand land to housing board in two weeks, Madhya Pradesh HC to official liquidator
news.para: The court directed the presence of an additional commissioner of municipal corporation during handing over possession of land to MPHIDB.

news.title: Lucknow: Registration date extended till January 21 for Akbarnagar residents
news.para: A total 14 registrations were done at the camp on Friday, with 10 individuals opting for houses under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY). So far, 81 people have registered for PMAY houses, while 88 have chosen schemes under the DUDA.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 24 months or 46? Zero-period relief for developers isn't a blanket one
news.para: The zero-period relief, for one, will not be a blanket one when dues of realtors are recalculated. The Kant committee had suggested two zero periods, one for Covid (March 2020 to March 2022) and the other for construction curbs because of NGT orders (August 2013 to June 2015).

news.title: About 134 extra flats built without nod, HC wants probe by Ghaziabad development body
news.para: Officials said the developer of Express Garden in Vaibhav Khand had carved out 536 flats against the 402 units for which it had taken approval from GDA.
